Taiwan Stocks Mover: China Steel Chemical, Powertech Technology

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-04-07T05:59:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/taiwan-stocks-mover-china-steel-chemical-inotera-memories.html
Stocks of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close.  The Taiex Index rose 49.74, or 0.6 percent, to 8,901.72.  China Steel Chemical Corp. (1723)  (1723 TT), a maker of chemicals
for steel, advanced 1.9 percent to a record NT$165. The
company’s first-quarter net income rose to NT$602 million, the
company said in a statement to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange . This
compares to NT$413 million in the same period a year earlier,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Powertech Technology Inc. (6239)  (6239 TT) gained 2.6 percent to
NT$100.50, the highest since March 11. The chip test service
provider was rated “buy” in new coverage at Goldman Sachs
Group Inc., which said the stock’s valuation is “undemanding”
and that the company’s operating margin could “trend up” in
the next two quarters. The brokerage has a share-price forecast
of NT$120, according to a report by Edward Yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
